<t>CREATE TABLE Hotel (
    hotel_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    location VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    rating FLOAT
);

CREATE TABLE Room (
    room_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    hotel_id INT REFERENCES Hotel(hotel_id),
    room_type VARCHAR(50),
    price DECIMAL(10, 2),
    capacity INT
);

CREATE TABLE Booking (
    booking_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    room_id INT REFERENCES Room(room_id),
    guest_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    check_in_date DATE,
    check_out_date DATE,
    total_price DECIMAL(10, 2)
);</t><stat>SELECT * FROM Hotel;</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE Hotel (

    booking_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,

    guest_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    check_in_date DATE,
    check_out_date DATE,

CREATE TABLE Booking (
    booking_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    room_id INT REFERENCES Room(room_id),
    guest_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    check_in_date DATE,
    check_out_date DATE,
    total_price DECIMAL(10, 2)
);

CREATE TABLE Hotel (
    hotel_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    location VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    rating FLOAT
);</t><stat>select h.name, avg(b.total_price) as average_booking_price from hotel h join room r on h.hotel_id = r.hotel_id join booking b on r.room_id = b.room_id group by h.name;</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE Booking (
    booking_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    room_id INT REFERENCES Room(room_id),
    guest_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    check_in_date DATE,
    check_out_date DATE,
    total_price DECIMAL(10, 2)
);

CREATE TABLE Hotel (
    hotel_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    location VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    rating FLOAT
);

CREATE TABLE Room (
    room_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    hotel_id INT REFERENCES Hotel(hotel_id),
    room_type VARCHAR(50),
    price DECIMAL(10, 2),
    capacity INT
);</t><stat>SELECT h.name, AVG(b.total_price) AS average_booking_price FROM Hotel h JOIN Room r ON h.hotel_id = r.hotel_id JOIN Booking b ON r.room_id = b.room_id GROUP BY h.name;</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE Booking (
    booking_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,

    check_in_date DATE,
    check_out_date DATE,

CREATE TABLE Booking (
    booking_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    room_id INT REFERENCES Room(room_id),
    guest_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    check_in_date DATE,
    check_out_date DATE,
    total_price DECIMAL(10, 2)
);</t><stat>SELECT h.name, MAX(b.total_price) AS max_booking_price FROM Hotel h JOIN Room r ON h.hotel_id = r.hotel_id JOIN Booking b ON r.room_id = b.room_id GROUP BY h.name;</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE Hotel (
    hotel_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    location VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    rating FLOAT
);
